Lane polylogue-terminal-note, worktree = your cwd, branch feature/fanout/terminal-note.
MISSION: polylogue-dmp — 'polylogue note': zero-friction memory capture from the terminal, landing as candidate assertions through the existing judgment gate. OWN: new CLI verb module + tests. AVOID: cli startup/routing internals (another lane owns those files), judge TUI (another lane).
Read the bead(s) fully with bd show (description, design, AC, notes) before coding; prework packets are accelerators, not authority. Worker-owned verification: focused devtools test + anti-vacuity statement per test. Commit AND push every logical chunk. Do NOT close/claim beads; report per-bead AC status in the PR body. Open a PR (Summary/Problem/Solution/Verification, Ref polylogue-<id>); do not merge. Never touch the live archive root.
